This paper deals with the propagation of a virus or competing idea/product over a social network, which is a classic problem in the field of social network analysis. The paper focuses on the impact of different profiles on the spread of the virus, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of social network analysis (cs.SOC). Additionally, the paper uses theoretical and experimental methods to analyze the problem, which involves the use of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) as well as network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also deals with the steady state of the network, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper provides bounds on certain properties of the network, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
